MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
Hollywood Pictures, a newly formed division of Disney Studios, has signed 
Goldie Hawn in its first major talent agreement. Hawn will star in seven films 
for Hollywood, and may produce some or all of them as well. The deal also 
allows her to produce other projects developed by her company. Also upcoming on 
Hawn's schedule is a picture for Universal -- "Bird on a Wire," an action 
comedy in which she stars with Mel Gibson. ALEENE MacMINN 
